PTRANSFORMER(1)               General Commands Manual                PTRANSFORMER(1)

NAME
       ptransformer - Local image/PDF conversion web tool

SYNOPSIS
       ptransformer [--port PORT] [--quality QUALITY] [--help]

DESCRIPTION
       PicTransformer is a local web-based tool that supports batch image to
       JPEG conversion, PDF merging, and image to PDF conversion.

OPTIONS
       --port PORT
              Set the server port (default: 5000)

       --quality QUALITY
              Set default JPEG quality 1-100 (default: 95)

       --secret-key KEY
              Set Flask secret key. Falls back to PICTRANSFORMER_SECRET_KEY
              environment variable if not provided.

       --help
              Show this help message

USAGE
       Start the server:
              ./start.sh

       Open http://127.0.0.1:5000 in your browser (or custom --port)

       Supported image formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, BMP, GIF, TIFF, WebP, TIF,
       HEIC, HEIF, SVG, ICO, PSD, RAW, AVIF

FILES
       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/
              Default installation directory

       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/uploads/
              Temporary storage for uploaded images

       ~/Dev/Pictransformer/converted/
              Temporary storage for converted JPEG files

EXAMPLES
       Start with default settings:
              ./start.sh

       Start on custom port:
              python3 app.py --port 8080

       Start with custom default quality:
              python3 app.py --quality 85

